{
  "_comment": [
    "Provisional tolerances for sensevoice-small. Derived per-tensor from",
    "reference-side magnitude statistics:",
    "  max_abs  = max(1e-4 * p99_abs, 1e-6)   # 0.01% of typical large value",
    "  mean_abs = max(1e-5 * rms,     1e-6)   # 0.001% of RMS energy",
    "p99_abs and rms are read from the ref sidecars under",
    "build/validate/sensevoice/sensevoice-small/<case>/<stage_dir>/ref/.",
    "When the same tensor name appears in multiple (case, stage_dir),",
    "we take the max p99_abs / rms across instances so the budget",
    "covers the worst-magnitude case.",
    "",
    "These multipliers (1e-4 / 1e-5) are roughly 10x looser than the",
    "typical fp32-vs-fp32 cross-library drift (~1e-5 relative) and well",
    "below Wilkinson worst-case (~1e-4 for stacked matmuls), so a",
    "correctly-ported tensor lands at or below this budget on first",
    "Stage 4 run, while real porting bugs (wrong epsilon, missing",
    "residual, scale factor off, unintended dtype upcast) trip it.",
    "The 1e-6 floor catches near-zero tensors where the relative budget",
    "would otherwise vanish (zero-init biases, all-zero pad regions).",
    "",
    "Provisional \u2014 Stage 4 finalizes against observed C++ drift. Do NOT",
    "ship the model while any entry still carries _provisional: true."
  ],
